<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRUG CZAR WILLIAM BENNETT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
So Bennett came to California and urged the state Senate to create a bill that 
would re-criminalize marijuana here. Gov. George Deukmejian says if such a bill 
comes to him, he will not hesitate to sign it. 
</P>
<P>
What I would like to know is where do Bennett and Deukmejian plan to put the 
several hundred thousand people who use marijuana when it's time to incarcerate 
them and how do they plan to pay for the law enforcement, court costs and 
prisons? 
</P>
<P>
Deukmejian has repeatedly cut funds for family planning, education and health 
care yet he thinks California can afford to pay for this absurd notion? I think 
not. 
</P>
<P>
DEBORAH BARNES 
</P>
<P>
San Bernardino 
</P>
