<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOME HELP AT HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the streets of Iran, where once there were thousands of Iranian citizens 
chanting slogans such as "America Is the Great Satan" and "Death to America," 
we now find thousands of them suddenly homeless, hungry and dying in the 
streets. 
</P>
<P>
We Americans are asked to put our political differences aside and view this 
situation strictly as a humanitarian issue. 
</P>
<P>
I find it difficult to believe that the dispensing of funds and medical 
supplies to Iran could possibly be viewed as anything less than a political 
act. 
</P>
<P>
However, I do believe there is a significant humanitarian issue here that 
should be raised. If there are funds and medical supplies available to be used 
for humanitarian aide, then it should first be used to help the thousands of 
those who are homeless, hungry and dying in the streets of America. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN WOODS 
</P>
<P>
Brea 
</P>
</TEXT>
