HOT TOPICS: HIGH LIFE: A WEEKLY FORUM FOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS; 
</P>
<P>
HOW WOULD IT BE TO POSSESS SUPERHUMAN POWERS? WHY, JUST SUPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Did you ever wish you could streak across the sky like Superman or float 
through walls like Casper? Who can watch Saturday morning cartoons or read 
about the Olympian gods and goddesses without envying their superhuman 
capabilities? 
</P>
<P>
At one time or another all of us have desired an ability or two that would set 
us apart from ordinary mortals. Hot Topics wonders, "If you could have any 
super power, which would you choose? Why?" 
</P>
<P>
"To be able to hear things really far away, so you could hear things people 
said about you." 
</P>
<P>
Jeanine Cronin, 17, senior, Laguna Hills 
</P>
<P>
"Putting thoughts in friends' heads without talking, because sometimes the 
words come out wrong." 
</P>
