<HEADLINE>
<P>
DESECRATE FLAG, GO TO PRISON, CHINESE TOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese who desecrate the national flag can be imprisoned for up to three years 
under a law passed Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The nation's first flag law, adopted by the Standing Committee of the National 
People's Congress, also forbids the use of the emblem in advertisements or as a 
trademark, the official New China News Agency said. 
</P>
<P>
Willful damage to a flag is punishable by up to three years of imprisonment, 
detention, surveillance or deprivation of political rights. 
</P>
<P>
The new law takes effect Oct. 1, China's national day. 
</P>
