<P>
BENSONHURST JURY SAYS IT'S DEADLOCKED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jurors deliberating the fate of the third young man to be tried in the 
Bensonhurst racial slaying announced Thursday that they were deadlocked over a 
verdict in the racially charged case, but the judge told them to keep trying. 
Appearing tired and frustrated, the jurors told state Justice Thaddeus Owens on 
the fourth day of their deliberations that they could not reach a consensus on 
several of the counts against John Vento, charged with murder for allegedly 
helping recruit a white group that killed a black teen-ager. Both juries in the 
previous Bensonhurst trial announced in the middle of their deliberations that 
they were deadlocked, and both eventually reached verdicts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
