<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLE WATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Toon Award: Warner Bros. cartoon director Chuck Jones will be among the 
recipients of the American Academy of Achievement's Golden Plate award in 
Chicago Saturday. The Academy cited the three-time Oscar-winner and creator of 
Pepe LePew, Wile E. Coyote and the Road Runner as "a modern master of animated 
films, a comic genius (who has) brought laughter to millions throughout the 
world." GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
