</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Local TV and radio stations will provide live coverage of much of Nelson 
Mandela's visit to Los Angeles today. 
</P>
<P>
KCBS Channel 2 and KTTV Channel 11 will begin coverage of the entertainment at 
City Hall at 10:30 a.m., with KNBC Channel 4 joining at 11:30 a.m. They and 
KCAL-TV Channel 9 will broadcast Mandela's speech at noon. 
</P>
<P>
KCBS also plans to cover Mandela's address at the Los Angeles Coliseum, 
probably about 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Among the radio stations that will be broadcasting the visiting South African 
anti-apartheid leader's actiivites will be KCRW-FM (89.9), KFWB-AM (980), 
KGFJ-AM (1230) and KNX-AM (1070). 
