WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
COLOMBIA; 
</P>
<P>
14 KILLED, 33 INJURED BY MEDELLIN BOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 14 people were killed and 33 wounded in the cocaine capital of 
Medellin, Colombia, when a car bomb exploded near a police station just as the 
city's new police chief was being sworn in, authorities said. No one claimed 
responsibility for the blast, but authorities blamed the Medellin drug 
traffickers, who have been waging a terror campaign. The bomb left a large 
crater and heavily damaged vehicles and buildings nearby. 
</P>
