<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : CAMP PENDLETON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Brig. Gen. Richard Huckaby retired Thursday after 31 years in the Marine Corps 
and turned over his command of Camp Pendleton to Maj. Gen. John Monahan. 
</P>
<P>
Monahan, who already commands I Marine Expeditionary Force and the 1st Marine 
Division, will command the base until late summer. 
</P>
<P>
Then, Maj. Gen. Walter E. Boomer, who commands the 4th Marine Division based in 
New Orleans, will replace Monahan as commander of Camp Pendleton and the I 
Marine Expeditionary Force. 
</P>
<P>
A new commanding general for the 1st Marine Division, which is the ground 
combat part of the expeditionary force, will be announced soon. 
</P>
