<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 32-year-old East San Diego man shot himself in the head at his residence 
after fleeing a minor hit-run accident, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Shortly after 11 p.m. Wednesday, Paul Michael Burke hit another car at College 
Avenue and Meridian Avenue, police spokesman Bill Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
After the accident, a witness followed Burke to his residence, a converted 
garage in the 5700 block of Redwood Street, officials said. The witness 
notified a police officer who was impounding a car a few houses away. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the officer approached the house and heard a single gunshot. More 
officers were called to the residence, surrounded it, and attempted to contact 
Burke by telephone. 
</P>
<P>
Officers entered the residence after midnight, Robinson said, and found Burke 
dead of a self-inflicted shotgun blast to the head. 
</P>
</TEXT>
