<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: FERRY'S DEAL COULD GROW TO $34 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rookie Danny Ferry's contract with the Cleveland Cavaliers will pay him at 
least $14 million over the next five years, but could ultimately become a 
10-year, $34-million deal, the Akron Beacon Journal reported Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Ferry, the former Duke star who played professionally in Italy last season, 
signed with the Cavaliers earlier this month. The newspaper said Ferry got a 
$1-million signing bonus and an annual salary beginning at $2 million and 
escalating to $3.3 million in the fifth year. 
</P>
<P>
Either party can get out of the contract at that point under certain 
conditions. If the deal continues, Ferry could get $4 million for each of the 
ensuing five years. 
</P>
