<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: CHARGERS SIGN NEBRASKA LINEBACKER MILLS, A 
THIRD-ROUND DRAFT PICK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CURT HOLBREICH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chargers Thursday announced the signing of third-round draft choice Jeff 
Mills, an outside linebacker from Nebraska. 
</P>
<P>
Mills, 6-feet-3 1/2 and 238 pounds, is the first of 17 Charger draft choices to 
sign. He was the first of three Charger picks in the third round, the 57th 
player selected overall. 
</P>
<P>
Charger General Manager Bobby Beathard said he hoped signing Mills would help 
speed the signing of the Chargers' other third-round choices -- offensive 
tackle Leo Goeas of Hawaii and wide receiver Walter Wilson of East Carolina. 
</P>
<P>
Beathard said Mills signed a series of three one-year contracts plus an option 
year. Financial details were not released. CURT HOLBREICH 
</P>
</TEXT>
