<P>
KABUKI: The Grand Kabuki of Japan, appearing this weekend at the Orange County 
Performing Arts Center, survives in part because of Faubion Bowers, one-time 
secretary to Gen. Douglas MacArthur. . . . Bowers tried to persuade the general 
to lift the ban on Kabuki in postwar Japan, "but he was a cultural numskull. He 
never went to a concert, never went to a play, never read a book -- except the 
Bible. 'Kabuki?' he said. 'What's that?' " 
