<TEXT>
<P>
HOT TOPIC: The county heat records falling this week (B1) were set in 1907 when 
heat was harder to handle. . . . The Santa Ana Daily Evening Blade reported an 
"ice famine," in which ice was rationed for refrigerators only. . . . Ice 
shipments from Los Angeles were stopped at the height of the heat wave, causing 
intense resentment here. . . . June has long been a freakish month in Orange 
County. The highest June temperature occurred early in the month (112 degrees 
on June 1, 1879), but a meager 87-degree record for June 14 has stood for 86 
years. 
</P>
