ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
CITY COMPILES TIPS ON REDUCING TRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As part of a campaign to inform residents about a new recycling program, the 
city has compiled a list of tips for reducing the amount of garbage generated 
by each household. 
</P>
<P>
The tips, published in the city hall newsletter, include buying products in 
bulk quantities with minimal, recyclable packaging; avoiding disposable items 
such as Styrofoam, paper plates or disposable diapers, and donating used 
appliances and furniture to charities so the items can be used again. 
</P>
<P>
The city General Services Department has also provided the name of a company 
that offers to remove names from some bulk mail lists to reduce the amount of 
paper thrown away as junk mail. Interested residents can write to the Mail 
Preference Service, Direct Marketing Assn., Six E. 43rd St., P.O. Box 3861, 
Grand Central Station. New York, N.Y. 10163-3861. 
</P>
</TEXT>
