<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
CITY PLANS SPECIAL TRASH COLLECTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents of Costa Mesa can now do some summer cleaning to get rid of oversize 
items and save a trip to the dump at the same time. 
</P>
<P>
For the eighth year, city officials approved a special citywide trash pickup 
for eight weeks beginning this week. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council agreed to pay Costa Mesa Disposal Inc. $31,130 to handle the 
project, in addition to $7,235 in dump charges. Residents will receive notices 
one week before their pickup date. 
</P>
<P>
Special pickup items should be kept separate from regular trash but put in the 
same location. Crews will pick up mattresses, refrigerators, water heaters, 
washers and dryers, stoves, sofas, lumber and furniture. Workers will not pick 
up tires, tree limbs, asphalt, cars, chemicals, hazardous waste, concrete, 
dirt, oil drums or paint cans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
