<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: K MART WINS BATTLE WITH THREE D 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three D Departments Inc., operator of bed and bath specialty stores, lost a 
round Thursday in its 3 1/2-year breach-of-contract lawsuit against K mart 
Corp. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. District Court in Chicago granted K mart a summary judgment dismissing 
claims by Three D that K mart violated a contract in November, 1986, when it 
closed 30 Designer Depot stores in which Three D operated leased bed and bath 
departments. 
</P>
<P>
Three D spokesman Frank Kane said the company plans to appeal the court's 
decision. K mart officials could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
<P>
Kane said Three D, which operates 33 stores, is asking for unspecified damages 
in the case. 
</P>
<P>
For the nine months ended April 28, the company reported earnings of $514,000 
on sales of $30.9 million, compared with net income of $639,000 on sales of 
$29.5 million in the year-earlier period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
