<TEXT>
<P>
Irving Wallace, who wrote the best-selling novels "The Chapman Report" and "The 
Prize," was hospitalized in serious condition today with pancreatic cancer, a 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Wallace, 74, entered Cedars-Sinai Medical Center on Tuesday. 
</P>
