P. M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
CANADA TRUCKERS BAR U.S. LANE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WINDSOR, Canada 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 30 Canadian truckers blocked a lane of truck traffic bound for the United 
States today, the second protest in five weeks over high taxes and government 
policies they say threaten their livelihood. 
</P>
<P>
The parked trucks did not impede cars from crossing the Ambassador Bridge 
between Detroit and Windsor as traffic moved freely in another northbound lane 
of Route 401. 
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, about 12 trucks parked along the Peace Bridge between Ft. Erie, 
Ont., and Buffalo, N.Y., shortly after midnight. 
</P>
<P>
Despite the truckers' call for a nationwide border protest, no other blockades 
were reported along the 4,000-mile U.S.-Canadian frontier. 
</P>
<P>
The drivers say they are losing work to U.S. truckers who pay less for fuel and 
have lower taxes and insurance costs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
