<HEADLINE>
<P>
RIGAMAJIG CAPTURES $33,000 TERPSICHORIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rigamajig slipped through between horses to take the lead in the deep stretch 
and then held on to win a neck victory in the $33,000 Terpsichorist purse for 
fillies and mares 3-years-and-up at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
Noble Links was runner-up in the eight-horse field another neck ahead of Le 
Famo. 
</P>
<P>
The win was the third in seven starts this year for Rigamajig who covered one 
mile and a quarter on the firm Inner Turf Course in 1:59:3 to earn $19,800 and 
return $19.00, $8.40 and $7.00. Noble Links paid $10.00 and $5.00 and Le Famo 
was $4.20. 
</P>
